00:52:23.550 --> 00:52:26.190
I'm looking.

00:52:26.190 --> 00:52:29.240
Oh. To Ben Ivans.

00:52:29.240 --> 00:52:30.290
&gt;&gt; Ben Ivans: Question
for Chris.

00:52:30.290 --> 00:52:33.360
You had -- if I understand
correctly --

00:52:33.360 --> 00:52:38.150
were noting that neither
compulsory licenses nor

00:52:38.150 --> 00:52:40.840
collective agreements --

00:52:40.840 --> 00:52:45.780
ASCAP/BMI consent
agreements address this issue.

00:52:45.780 --> 00:52:51.580
Do you know if the songwriter
community has ever sought either

00:52:51.580 --> 00:52:53.940
of those to be included?

00:52:53.940 --> 00:52:57.980
I mean, have they have said
in ASCAP/BMI negotiations,

00:52:57.980 --> 00:52:59.750
"We want to negotiate this"?

00:52:59.750 --> 00:53:01.920
Have they ever talked about 115

00:53:01.920 --> 00:53:05.330
or whatever saying this should
be an additional element,

00:53:05.330 --> 00:53:08.300
or have they not pushed that --

00:53:08.300 --> 00:53:09.130
&gt;&gt; Chris Castle:
I'm not aware of it.

00:53:09.130 --> 00:53:12.300
But then again, the compulsory
license rate was two cents

00:53:12.300 --> 00:53:14.520
for 65 years or so, you know.

00:53:14.520 --> 00:53:19.900
So I don't know why that is, but
